BACKGROUND: Despite significant improvement in clinical care, operative 
strategies, and technology, neurosurgery is still risky, and optimal 
preoperative planning and anatomical assessment are necessary to minimize the 
risks of serious complications. Our purpose was to document the dural venous 
sinuses (DVS) and their variations identified during routine 3-dimensional (3D) 
venography created through 3D models for the teaching of complex cerebral 
